main event: Witness observed bright silvery lighted objects in the shape of cylinders with domes over Wheeling, W.Va., on 29 October 63.
interesting points: The objects were observed at several thousand feet in altitude,The sighting occurred in bright daylight,The witness reported no sound emitted from the objects,The objects were seen at a course southeast from the observing location,The conclusion of the sighting suggests it could be Venus or a possible meteorite or comet.
sighted object: bright silvery lighted cylindrical objects with domes
witness description: Witness lived in Wheeling for 30 years and believes in UFOs.
